From: Eryone X400 Migration <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 15 May 2026 00:00:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] klippy: suppress chamber verify_heater debug response

Legacy X400 build commented out noisy chamber heater debug responses. This is
kept as a temporary patch artifact pending replacement with configurable
logging behavior in an out-of-tree extra.
---
 klippy/extras/verify_heater.py | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/klippy/extras/verify_heater.py b/klippy/extras/verify_heater.py
index 1d087ab..4cca382 100644
--- a/klippy/extras/verify_heater.py
+++ b/klippy/extras/verify_heater.py
@@ -46,8 +46,8 @@ class HeaterCheck:
             reactor.update_timer(self.check_timer, reactor.NEVER)
     def check_event(self, eventtime):
         temp, target = self.heater.get_temp(eventtime)
-        if "chamber_heater" in self.heater_name and self.error:
-            self.printer.lookup_object('gcode').respond_info("%.2f C：%.2f" % (temp,self.error))
+        #if "chamber_heater" in self.heater_name and self.error:
+        #    self.printer.lookup_object('gcode').respond_info("%.2f C：%.2f" % (temp,self.error))
         if temp >= target - self.hysteresis or target <= 0.:
             # Temperature near target - reset checks
             if self.approaching_target and target:
-- 
